<section class="cat-page-faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cat-page-faq-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked questions</span>
      <h2>What we are most often asked about massages.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="cat-page-faq-list">
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item open">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Which modality for what? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Cervical tension/headaches: cranio-facial-cervical. Heavy legs: tired legs or aloe vera. Tired feet or reflex issues: reflexology. General anti-fatigue: body or relaxing. Deep facial care: collagen or vitamin C facial.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Ideal frequency? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>It depends on the goal. General maintenance: once a month. Chronic tension: every 2-3 weeks until resolved. Facials: every 4-6 weeks combined with cleansing.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Cranio-facial-cervical massage for migraines? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Yes, particularly useful for tension headaches and migraines originating in the cervical area. It does not replace medical treatment but complements it significantly.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Pregnancy? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Yes, with adapted modality and position. A relaxing massage with a gentle technique is perfectly safe. Avoid reflex points on the feet during the first trimester.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">What is reflexology massage and why reflexological? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>The foot has zones that mirror organs of the body. Stimulating these zones with the right technique can ease distant tensions (headache, digestive fatigue, lower-back pain). More than a foot massage — it is whole-body work.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

